CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 9, 1972, pg. 1 reads: "Join Our Struggle - Demonstrators who assembled outside Western Penitentiary in support of the Sept. 5th work stoppage are asking those who wish to "quietly" support the strike, do so by calling, writing, or sending a telegram to their state legislators-making it known that the public backs the strike. (Harris Photo)
TitMainTitle: Demonstrators holding up protest signs against prison conditions, including one reading "Striking for Humane Treatment," standing on train tracks along Ohio River, near Western Penitentiary
